\pard\f0\fs28 Several species produce dimorphic seeds. The first-formed are black, shining, smooth or with a fine pattern on the testa; the later-formed are larger, light brown or olive, dull, with a distinct, coarse reticulum on the testa. The seeds referred to in this account are always the first-formed seeds.
\par

