\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. S. physophora} Pallas,{\i }{\i  Ill. Pl.} 51 (1803). Small shrub up to 120 cm. Leaves 20-40 × 1-2 mm, filiform, obtuse or subacute. Cymes very lax. Fruiting perianth spongy-inflated, reddish. Seeds punctate, mostly horizontal.{\i  S.E. Russia, W. Kazakhstan}. Rs(E). ({\i C. Asia.})
\par

