\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. S. dendroides} (C.A. Meyer) Moq., {\i Chenop. Monogr. Enum. }126 (1840). Small shrub up to 60 cm. Leaves 5-16 × 1-2 mm, semicylindrical, obtuse, attenuate at the base. Cymes dense; peduncle connate with the base of the bract. Fruiting perianth inflated, green. Seeds more or less smooth, mostly horizontal. {\i S.E. Russia, W. Kazakhstan.} Rs(E). ({\i Caspian region}.)
\par

