\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. S. baccifera} Pallas,{\i  Ill. Pl.} 48 (1803). Annual up to 50 cm, often woody at the base. Leaves 12-25 × 0·6-1 mm, semi-cylindrical, mostly obtuse. Cymes dense. Fruiting perianth much enlarged, baccate, red. Seeds smooth, mostly horizontal.{\i  S. Russia; one locality in E. Ukraine}. Rs(W, E).
